Fairly fast lens - A fast lens will have a 'wide open' aperture of 1.8 or 2.8. Because it is counter-intuitive, consider it as a fraction. An aperture of F22 would be 1/22 which is a small number and would be a small opening. An aperture of F1.8 would be 1/1.8 and would be wide open and a larger opening. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/ad/440830-1b2.JPG/v4-459px-440830-1b2.JPG","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/ad/440830-1b2.JPG/v4-759px-440830-1b2.JPG","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Image by: Uploader<br>
